

//Run Xampp-1

how to open xampp
 =================================
go to Downloads and open Terminal
run command : sudo ./xampp-linux-x64-7.3.33-0-installer.run
=================================                                                                                                           
 open another terminal
run command : sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start




// When services is stop then you can you there is command-2


hlink@hlink-System-Product-Name:~/Downloads$ sudo./xampp-linux-x64-7.3.33-0-installer.run
bash: sudo./xampp-linux-x64-7.3.33-0-installer.run: No such file or directory
hlink@hlink-System-Product-Name:~/Downloads$ sudo service mysql stop
[sudo] password for hlink: 
hlink@hlink-System-Product-Name:~/Downloads$ sudo /opt/lampp/lampp strat
Usage: lampp <action>

	start         Start XAMPP (Apache, MySQL and eventually others)
	startapache   Start only Apache
	startmysql    Start only MySQL
	startftp      Start only ProFTPD

	stop          Stop XAMPP (Apache, MySQL and eventually others)
	stopapache    Stop only Apache
	stopmysql     Stop only MySQL
	stopftp       Stop only ProFTPD

	reload        Reload XAMPP (Apache, MySQL and eventually others)
	reloadapache  Reload only Apache
	reloadmysql   Reload only MySQL
	reloadftp     Reload only ProFTPD

	restart       Stop and start XAMPP
	security      Check XAMPP's security

	enablessl     Enable SSL support for Apache
	disablessl    Disable SSL support for Apache

	backup        Make backup file of your XAMPP config, log and data files

	oci8          Enable the oci8 extenssion

	panel         Starts graphical XAMPP control panel

hlink@hlink-System-Product-Name:~/Downloads$ sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start
Starting XAMPP for Linux 7.3.33-0...
XAMPP: Starting Apache...already running.
XAMPP: Starting MySQL...ok.
XAMPP: Starting ProFTPD...already running.
hlink@hlink-System-Product-Name:~/Downloads$ 

